item.title: Forward-Deployed Engineer (FDE) - EUROPE AND LATIN AMERICA, USA and Canada Applicants - Upwork
item.description:
Forward-Deployed Engineer (FDE)
YOU NEED TO BE ABLE TO WORK IN NEW YORK TIME ZONE!!!
BE FLUENT IN ENGLISH!!!
Type: Remote | Full-time

Job Description:

Language Requirements:
Fluent in English

About You
â— You are a hands-on expert in system integration, data warehousing (or at least ETL specification and development), and reporting.
â— You are experienced at team leadership: assigning work, managing delivery, and addressing risks and issues. Initially, you will have only two people to share tasks with. But, the team will grow as our customer

Responsibilities
Customer Onboarding
â— You will work alongside and in lock step with Sales, Product and Customer Success directly with customers during the onboarding of new customers on the company SaaS platform.
â— You will define and implement processes that enable you to collect customer-specific implementation requirements and configurations and oversee smooth implementation for each customer.
â— Working with the Customer Success Team, you will determine how the customer plans to use the company’s system and the data that the customer will supply. You will rely on your strong communication and interpersonal skills to build relationships and ensure everyone is aligned.
â— Reporting
â—‹ You will work with customers to understand reporting requirements and recommend visualizations.
â— Customer Data Integration
â—‹ You will work with the customer to specify and implement client data integrations through third party APIs or flat file feeds.
â—‹ You will define and oversee the specification and development of ETL required to populate our application for each customer.
â—‹ You will specify customer-specific data model changes required to support reporting requirements and oversee the implementation of these changes.
â—‹ You will specify and oversee the implementation of any customizations to our platform required to allow us to comply with our customers’ information security and compliance requirements.
â—‹ You will oversee implementation of SSO connectivity between the company and customer systems
Human Resource Capacity Planning
â— You will develop and manage a capacity plan for your support team and formulate a staff management plan to support projected customer launches. (The data for this planning can come from our issue tracking system where we track time and from the insights you gain from managing customer implementations. Ideally, we can largely automate this capacity planning process.)
Customer Technical Support
â— You and your team will provide the customer ongoing support, troubleshooting issues, and ensuring optimal platform functioning and performance.
â— You will track and manage all customer technical issues through to successful resolution and communicate proactively with the customer. You will implement fixes and configurations yourself or project manage engineers who do it for you.
Product Development Support
â— You will work closely with our Product and Core Software Development Teams to champion the delivery of product and platform capabilities, features, and functions that improve the customer experience.
â— You will ensure that customers’ needs are prioritized and that the customers’ voices are heard throughout the product development process.

A Few Things We’re Looking For
â— Experience building a startup company from 0 to 1: we are going to need you to lead and establish and evolve processes
â— Experience team leading or project managing technical delivery; you are going to be a developer who is delegating to other developers.
â— Data Warehousing, data modeling, and ETL
â— Knowledge of the best ways to visualize data to answer questions and solve problems
â— Experience with enterprise BI tools such as Tableau and Power BI
â— Expertise in NodeJS, Typescript, JavaScript – that’s what our ETL is currently developed in though we could be convinced to switch technologies.
â— Exceptional common sense and the ability to manage ambiguity

Bonus
Experience in any of these areas is a bonus:
â— Building or using Financial Planning & Analysis systems
â— Global, enterprise SaaS development
â— ReactJS

Diverse Perspectives
We know that innovation thrives on teams where diverse points of view come together to solve hard problems in ways that are just now possible. As such, we explicitly seek people that bring diverse life experiences, diverse educational backgrounds, diverse cultures, and diverse work experiences. Please, be prepared to share with us how your perspective will bring something unique and valuable to our team as grows.

Hourly Range: $15.00-$35.00
Posted On: May 14, 2024 09:10 UTC
Category: Full Stack Development
Skills:JavaScript, TypeScript, Node.js, ETL, Microsoft Power BI Data Visualization, Data Warehousing, Data Modeling, SaaS Development, Project Management
Skills: JavaScript, TypeScript, Node.js, ETL, Microsoft Power BI Data Visualization, Data Warehousing, Data Modeling, SaaS Development, Project Management

item.title: E-Commerce Data Analyst - Upwork
item.description:
Job Overview:
We are seeking a highly analytical and detail-oriented Data Analyst to join our e-commerce team. In this role, you will be primarily responsible for interpreting and analyzing complex data sets to provide actionable insights that drive business decisions. You will work closely with our data engineering team to ensure data accuracy and accessibility, while focusing on data analysis, reporting, and visualization to support various departments across our company.

Responsibilities and Duties:
-Analyze large data sets to identify trends, patterns, and insights relevant to our e-commerce business.
-Develop and implement advanced data analysis, predictive modeling, and statistical techniques to solve complex business problems.
-Collaborate with the data engineering team to ensure seamless data collection and processing.
-Create and maintain rich interactive visualizations through data interpretation and analysis integrating various reporting components from multiple data sources.
-Define key performance indicators (KPIs) for business operations and develop automated dashboards and reports to track these metrics.
-Work with cross-functional teams to address data-related technical issues and support their data infrastructure needs.
-Conduct market research and competitor analysis to support strategic planning.
-Present findings and recommendations to key stakeholders and decision-makers.

Qualifications:
-Proven experience as a Data Analyst, preferably in e-commerce or a related field.
-Strong analytical skills with experience in statistical modeling and data analysis.
-Proficient in data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI) and Microsoft Excel.
-Familiarity with SQL and experience in querying databases.
-Excellent problem-solving abilities and attention to detail.
-Strong communication skills and ability to translate complex data into actionable insights.
-Bachelor’s degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Economics, or a related field.

Skills:
-Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a team environment.
-Strong time management and organizational skills.
-Passionate about data-driven decision making.


Hourly Range: $12.00-$15.00
Posted On: May 14, 2024 08:30 UTC
Category: Data Analytics
Skills:Tableau, Microsoft Power BI, Power Query, SQL, Microsoft Excel, Query Development, Data Analysis
Skills: Tableau, Microsoft Power BI, Power Query, SQL, Microsoft Excel, Query Development, Data Analysis
Country: Philippines

item.title: Power BI Administrator and Developer, with SQL Server data warehousing experience - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking a skilled Power BI Administrator and Developer with SQL Server data warehousing experience to join our team. As the Power BI Administrator and Developer, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining Power BI solutions to meet our business intelligence needs. You will also manage the Power BI environment, including data source connections, security, and performance optimization.

We intend to establish a long term relationship with the successful candidate.

    Responsibilities:
    - Designing and developing Power BI reports and dashboards
    - Creating data models and ETL processes
    - Troubleshooting and resolving Power BI issues
    - Collaborating with stakeholders to gather requirements and understand business needs
    - Implementing security measures to protect sensitive data
    - Monitoring and optimizing Power BI performance
    
    Requirements:
    - Proficiency in Power BI administration and development
    - Strong SQL Server data warehousing experience
    - Knowledge of data modeling and ETL processes
    - Familiarity with data visualization best practices
    - Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills
    - Strong communication and collaboration abilities

The role:
The successful candidate will work alongside a Business Analyst who will manage the requirement and project initiatives for a sales and marketing, pharmaceutical company with 3rd party manufacturers and logistics in South Africa.

The initial project:
1. Setup and secure the Power BI environment (migrating from Qlik Sense)
2. Redevelop existing NPrinting reports (Primarily Profit & Loss and Sales reporting) for dissemination
3. Decommission the Qlik Sense and NPrinting environment
4. Continue work on projects on a permanent basis, if successful
    
If you are a skilled Power BI Administrator and Developer looking to contribute to a dynamic team, please apply now.

item.title: Key data concepts, analysis, and techniques - Upwork
item.description:
In this assignment, you are tasked with conducting a data analysis project using Microsoft Azure on a provided dataset. Your submission should include a report, not exceeding 2000 words, detailing your approach to data analysis, the findings, and their interpretation.

Based on data set you need to answer the following questions:
Answer any 3
- Analyse the trend of total sales and profits over time.
- Compare the sales and profits of different states.
- Investigate the relationship between Discount and Profit. Create a scatter plot to visualise this relationship.
- Investigate the distribution of different ship modes.
- Identify the top 5 customers based on total sales. Create visualisations that compare these top customers in terms of sales, profit, and discount levels.
- Create a map to visualise sales and profit distributions by state.
- Analyse the frequency of orders by individual customers to identify loyal customers.
- Identify the top 10 selling products in terms of sales with visualisation.
- What is the predominant sub-category in terms of sales?
- Analyse the correlation between discount, profit and sales. Create a correlation heatmap to visualise this relationship.

item.title: ThoughtSpot/Looker Developer  - Upwork
item.description:
We are currently seeking a highly skilled ThoughtSpot or Looker Developer to join our esteemed IT team. The ideal candidate should possess a strong technical background in business intelligence, data science, and software engineering. As a part of this role, you will be responsible for the development of advanced business intelligence solutions using ThoughtSpot. This includes integrating complex data sources and deploying machine learning models to enhance analytical capabilities.

Key Responsibilities:

- Develop, deploy, and optimize ThoughtSpot solutions to meet intricate business requirements.
- Design and implement efficient data models within ThoughtSpot to support large-scale data analysis and reporting.
- Integrate ThoughtSpot with various data sources and platforms through the utilization of APIs and custom connectors.
- Collaborate with data scientists to implement and operationalize machine learning models within the ThoughtSpot environment.
- Compose advanced SQL queries and scripts to manipulate data and extend the functionalities of ThoughtSpot.
- Lead the design and execution of end-to-end system integrations, ensuring robustness and scalability.
- Monitor and troubleshoot ThoughtSpot applications, optimizing performance and resolving technical issues.
- Develop comprehensive documentation and provide technical training to stakeholders, enabling effective utilization of ThoughtSpot solutions.
- Stay updated with the latest developments in business intelligence, machine learning, and ThoughtSpot features to continuously enhance our solutions.

Required Qualifications:

- Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Engineering, or a related technical field.
- Minimum of 5 years of experience in business intelligence development, with a minimum of 5 years of focused experience in ThoughtSpot.
- Strong technical proficiency in SQL and experience with scripting languages like Python or R.
- Demonstrated experience with machine learning algorithms and their applications in business intelligence.
- Proven capability in handling large datasets and complex data structures.
- Solid understanding of data integration, ETL processes, and database optimization techniques.

Preferred Qualifications:

- Certifications in ThoughtSpot and other BI tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI).

item.title: PowerPoint Visual Designer - Upwork
item.description:
I'm looking to create a visual that represents my Data Warehouse Information Strategy

This visual ideally represents the following rings of concepts
1) The “tech” layers in a very simplified view
a. On-Premise Transactional databases that move data to
b. an Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) database that then moves data
c. Microsoft Azure Data Lake that then moves data to
d. PowerBI Semantic Models
2) The Data Sets that result from this
a. Artificial Intelligence (AI) data
b. Natural Language Processing (NLP) data
c. Study data
d. QA data
e. Facility data
f. Radiologist data
g. Billing data
h. Operations data
3) “Access” Layers which are the mechanisms to actually access the data as a user and are
a. Applications such as Order Management System
b. Governed Dashboards
c. Data exports from dashboards
d. Ad-hoc business user created dashboards
e. Querying model directly (SQL or Excel)
f. Direct excel access
g. Row level access via SQL, R, Python

I visualize this as "rings". In the inner ring is the tech layer that shows data moving from system to system. In the middle ring are the data sets available for consumption and in the outer ring as the final ways to access the data.

I'm looking for help building this visual.

Budget: $100

item.title: Power Apps User Interface Designer - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking a skilled Power Platform Developer specializing in both model-driven and canvas app design within Microsoft PowerApps. As part of our team, you will play a key role in developing intuitive and impactful user interfaces for our business applications. Your expertise will help us streamline processes and enhance user experiences across our organization.

Typically, you will work with an existing application that requires updates. A solution within the Power Platform will be created and packaged, including all necessary components, which will then be zipped and sent to you for import into your developer environment. This allows you to have full access to the schema. You will be responsible for performing the requested modifications or creating the new application interface. Once completed, you will repackage the updates and send them back for feedback and integration as an update to our current environment.

Responsibilities:
• Design and develop high-quality, functional user interfaces using Microsoft PowerApps.
• Work with model-driven and canvas apps to deliver tailored solutions to business challenges.
• Collaborate to gather requirements and translate business needs into technical specifications.
• Document all stages of design and development for future reference and compliance.

Requirements:
• Must have access to a Microsoft 365 Development environment and utilize the Power Platform Solutions functionality to transfer work product.
• Proven experience in developing with Microsoft PowerApps, focusing on both model-driven and canvas apps.
• Proven experience with other Power Platform tools and how they work within the ecosystem. This includes Power Automate, Power Bi, Copilot Studio (former Power Virtual Agents)
• Strong understanding of UI/UX principles and ability to apply them in creating user-friendly designs.
• Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work independently or as part of a team.
• Proficient in Microsoft Dataverse and familiar with its integration within PowerApps.
• Ability to communicate effectively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

Preferred Qualifications:
• Candidates with a portfolio that includes samples or examples of previous PowerApps projects will be given preference. Please provide links or attachments with your application.
• Experience building Microsoft Teams applications and customizations, including custom meeting stages.
• SharePoint Framework (SPFx) knowledge and ability to build SharePoint customizations or modify existing applications to be integrated as Web Parts, Single Page Apps (SPA) or application customizations.


Hourly Range: $15.00-$39.00

item.description:
We're searching for a skilled Grafana dev to create captivating visualizations of our data set based upon streaming logs.
